<p><img id="{F106EC4E-F307-446B-A0B3-B330687E82E6}" title="" alt="CHINA-BEIJING-XI JINPING-KIM JONG UN-TALKS (CN)" src="137070598_15221965261641n.jpg" sourcedescription="ç½ä¸æåçæä»¶" sourcename="æ¬å°æä»¶" /></p>
<p>Xi Jinping (2nd R), general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and Chinese president, and his wife Peng Liyuan (1st R) meet with Kim Jong Un (2nd L), chairman of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK) and chairman of the State Affairs Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), and his wife Ri Sol Ju at the Great Hall of the People in Beijing, capital of China. At the invitation of Xi, Kim paid an unofficial visit to China from March 25 to 28. During the visit, Xi held talks with Kim. (Xinhua/Ju Peng)</p>
